The paper deals with the design of a group sparse precoding scheme for a cloud radio access network (C-RAN) with multiple antennas at each user. This involves efficient resource allocation and interference management, which are key topics in the field of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also mentions compressive sensing theory, which is a subfield of signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of block diagonalization precoding, which is a technique commonly used in multimedia systems (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes an efficient algorithm based on Lagrangian dual, which is a method used in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
